data.title: WWE SummerSlam 1993
data.text:
August 30, 1993 – Auburn Hills, Michigan (The Palace)

[ Summerslam 1993 Gallery ]

SINGLES MATCH

Razor Ramon defeated “The Million Dollar Man” Ted DiBiase: This was a spin-off match stemming from the 1-2-3 Kid’s debut..

WWF TAG TEAM TITLE MATCH

The Steiner Brothers (Scott & Rick Steiner) defeated The Heavenly Bodies (Jimmy Del Rey & Tom Prichard w/Jim Cornette) to retain the WWF Tag Team titles: The Steiner Brothers’ mother and sister were seated in the front row…

WWF INTERCONTINENTAL TITLE MATCH

Shawn Michaels w/Diesel defeated Mr. Perfect by COUNT OUT to retain the WWF Intercontinental title: Diesel interfered and caused Mr. Perfect to get counted out, thus Shawn Michaels was able to keep his title!

SINGLES MATCH

Irwin R. Schyster defeated The 1-2-3 Kid:

IN THE RING

Bret “The Hitman” Hart & Jerry “The King” Lawler + Doink: Jerry Lawler came to the ring on crutches and said he is not medically cleared to compete tonight! Lawler announced Doink The Clown as his self-appointed replacement for the match. Doink came out and threw confetti over the crowd, and then threw a bucket of water on Bruce Hart at ringside!

SINGLES MATCH:

Bret “Hitman” Hart defeated Doink the Clown w/Jerry Lawler to DQ: Bret Hart locked Doink into the Sharpshooter. Jerry Lawler jumped in the ring and broke his crutch over Bret Hart’s head! Bruce & Owen Hart had to be held back by WWF officials as Lawler continued to assult Bret Hart. WWF President Jack Tunney came down and ordered Jerry Lawler to have his match with Bret Hart!

KING OF THE RING MATCH

Jerry “The King” Lawler defeated Bret “Hitman” Hart by DQ: Bret Hart originally won the match after making Jerry Lawler submit to the Sharpshooter! The decision was reversed when and team of referees couldn’t get Bret Hart to release the hold! Lawler was declared the winner via disqualification and the Undisputed King Of The Ring..

SINGLES MATCH

Ludvig Borga defeated Marty Jannetty by submission:

SINGLES MATCH

The Undertaker defeated Giant Gonzalez w/Harvey Wippleman: Harvey Wippleman had posession of the Undertaker’s urn.. Midway through the match, Paul Bearer came to ringside carrying a black wreath. Wippleman tried to pick a fight with Bearer, but got knocked out cold with one punch! Paul Bearer once again took posession of the urn and clutched it against his heart! The Undertaker suddenly sat up and fought back and pinned Giant Gonzales.. After the match, Giant Gonzales dumped Harvey Wippleman..

SIX-MAN TAG TEAM MATCH: The Smoking Gunns (Billy & Bart Gunn) & Tatanka defeated The Headshrinkers (Samu & Fatu) & Bam Bam Bigelow:

IN THE RING

Randy Savage & Aaron Neville: Randy Savage introduced Aaron Neville, who sang the American National Anthem..
